The method returns a string that satisfies the following conditions:
- The string only contains the letters `'a'`, `'b'`, and `'c'`.
- The string does not contain any of `"aaa"`, `"bbb"`, or `"ccc"` as a substring.
- The string contains at most `a` occurrences of the letter `'a'`.
- The string contains at most `b` occurrences of the letter `'b'`.
- The string contains at most `c` occurrences of the letter `'c'`.
If there are multiple longest happy strings, the method can return any of them.
If there is no such string, the method returns the empty string `""`.
